<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 27.</note>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Davis</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                E. B. Washburne</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-09-06"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 6, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>If provisional government has actual control and possession of power, and
                            is acknowledged by French people, so as to be, in point of fact, <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> government, of which you will be able to
                            decide by the time this reaches you, you will not hesitate to recognize
                            it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>DAVIS, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>